						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">TailChao wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">One issue is that the LFSR is only 12-Bits. So your percussion will sound a little metallic (especially hi-hats).</div><br />One thing that has worked for me for hi-hats on NES is alternating between 93- and 32767-step sequences on successive frames. I wonder if alternating 63- and 4095-step LFSRs might work for you.</div>

