			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Interesting.  What about the 7800, Lynx, or PC-Engine?  Those all use some variant of the 6502 (some even say the PC-Engine was essentially an NES on steroids), and IIRC the Lynx got one homebrew game a few years back.  I am aware that no two consoles have the exact video or audio controllers, and data regarding the control input would need to be changed accordingly, but could one build an engine for, say, an NES game and then port it (with the needed alterations) to another 6502 based machine?  The 7800 would be a challenge since it works much like the 2600 did, and completely backwards from the NES, and the C64 would need a different code to get scrolling to work.  As you can tell, I don't know much about how different these machines are.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

