					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">By way of analogy ... the original Macintosh, the Genesis, the Neo Geo, the Amiga, the Atari ST, NeXT machines, really early Sun workstations (everything before the Sun 4), earlier Palm PDAs, and many other things, all used the 68000 or its descendants. Yet I don't think anyone would assert that it would be significantly easier to port a program from one to another solely because they use the same CPU.</div>

